items.headline: Welcome to the Ghost in the Shell Wiki
items.desc:
Ghost in the Shell, a Japanese Manga and Anime franchise created by the manga artist Masamune Shirow, and filmmakers Mamoru Oshii and Kenji Kamiyama.

This wiki is brought to you by an open volunteer community of GitS fans, who strive to collect and consolidate everything known about the GitS Universe. You are welcome to join us and help by contributing to this wiki.

items.name: Hellsing Wiki
items.title: Hellsing Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to The Hellsing Wiki
items.desc:
The Hellsing Organization, a secret branch of the British government, has long been battling supernatural threats to keep the people safe from creatures of the night. Its current leader, Sir Integra Hellsing, controls her own personal army to eliminate the undead beings, but even her highly trained soldiers pale in comparison to her most trusted vampire exterminator, Alucard, who is actually a powerful vampire himself. Along with Integra's mysterious butler and Alucard's new vampire minion, Seras Victoria, the Hellsing Organization must face not only regular ghouls and vampires, but a rivaling secret branch of the Vatican and an mysterious group of madmen spawned by a certain war over 50 years ago.
The original Hellsing manga by Kouta Hirano ran 10 volumes, finishing in 2008. The Hellsing anime followed a different storyline, but with the same main characters. The dub ran in the United States from October 4, 2003 to December 27, 2003 on Starz!'s Encore Action cable channel.
The Hellsing OVA started at 2006, once completed will features 10 Episodes and, unlike the anime, it follows the manga more closely.

items.name: Hell Girl (Jigoku Shoujo) Wiki
items.title: Hell Girl (Jigoku Shoujo) Wiki
items.headline: Welcome to the Hell Girl Wikia
items.desc: Jigoku Shoujo, known as Hell Girl in English, is an anime series currently consisting of three seasons. It has also been adapted later on into a manga series which is still ongoing, a live-action television series which has finished airing with a total of 12 episodes, and a few games and mini-games. These adaptations are not canon to the anime series and follow different storylines instead, though with core similarities to the anime. The story of the anime (and in fact the whole series) has a recurring theme of injustice, hatred, suffering, and revenge. Elements like violence, harsh language, trickery, blackmail, animal cruelty, torture, insanity, twisted and complex human emotions, and such are found from time to time. Therefore, the anime is not suitable for younger audiences and viewers, and is rated R-17+.

items.headline: Wiki Hellcats France
items.desc: Ce wiki tourne autour de la série TV Hellcats crée en 2010. Cette série raconte l'histoire de Marti, une étudiante qui après avoir perdu sa bourse d'étude en raison des coupes budgétaires et de l'attitude de sa mère, se joint à l'équipe de cheerleaders (couramment appelées pom-pom girls) de son université. Pour réaliser son rêve de devenir avocate et quitter Memphis et sa mère alcoolique, Marti Perkins est contrainte de rejoindre les Hellcats, la légendaire équipe de cheerleaders de l’université locale, afin d'obtenir une bourse d’études dont dépend de son avenir. La jeune femme se retrouve propulsée en pleine compétition, la coach des Hellcats étant déterminée à accéder aux championnats nationaux.

items.headline: Hey survivors, check out the No More Room In Hell Wiki
items.desc:
This is the wiki all about No More Room In Hell: a free zombie first person shooter available on Steam; which was first released as a Source Engine mod but is now a standalone game. 
No More Room In Hell puts up to 8 players in the same server fighting waves of zombies (in Survival mode) or completing levels (in Objective mode). The game has tons of features it makes one not believe it's free: but it is! And it has no pay-to-win "premium" items.
So what are you waiting for? Try No More Room In Hell today and join in on editing the Wiki!

items.headline: The Mistresses await your arrival
items.desc:
Mistresses Michaelis, Phantomhive, and Morgenstern have ruled the darkness for eons. They are quite intelligent, and love to play pranks on the creatures of the day, but they welcome any who wish to follow them and their ways.

The queens are triplet sisters, and balance out each other. Mistress Michaelis makes sure the others don’t step out of line, thus saving them from Mistress Morgenstern’s wrath. Mistress Morgenstern protects the triplets, thus making sure they know what it is to be banned. Mistress Phantomhive always sees the little things, thus making sure that justice is always present.


Come on into the darkness, little one.... We want you here to join us.

Eternally.
